Defendant Christopher J Stocks in court, in custody, with attorney Samuel W. Benedict.   Bryan C. Bayer appeared for the State of Wisconsin.

Sentencing arugment by Atty. Bayer and Atty. Benedict.  Statement by Kathy G., Tiffany W. and Christopher S..

The Court Orders the Following:

Imposed  Sentence of:

11 Years Imprisonment (Credit - 298 days )
- 6 Years of Initial Confinement
- 5 Years of Extended Supervision

Conditions of Extended Supervision:
-AODA Assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended;
-Mental Health Evaluation and follow through with any treatment recommended;
- No Use or Possession of  illegal drugs or drug paraphernalia;
- No Use or Possession of prescription drugs without a valid prescription;
- Any valid prescription drugs must be taken in the manner in which they are prescribed;
- Inform agent of all prescriptions;
- Sign Medical Release for Agent;
- Operate a Motor Vehicle with a Valid Drivers License;
- Within the first 6 months of ES obtain a valid driver's license;
- Maintain/Obtain full time employment;
- No contact with any of the victims in the read in files or conviction files;
- Provide DNA sample if not yet provided  and pay surcharge.

Restitution: $150.00 in 14CM1317 to Andrew W., $170.00 in 14CM1318 to La Belle Motel and Walinda A  Remaining restitution requesting will be set for hearing.  To be paid with 25% of prison earning only and then at the rate of $50.00 per month commencing the 4th month of extended supervision.

Costs: $278.00 
DNA Surcharge:  $250.00
(To be paid after restitution is paid in full)

Defendant is eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program
Defendant is eligible for the Substance Abuse Program
  Restitution hearing scheduled for June 2, 2015 at 11:00 am.
